Yeltsin to make radio address on summit . President Boris Yeltsin will deliver a radio address on Wednesday dealing with Russian foreign policy and the results of his summit with U . S . President Bill Clinton , the Kremlin press service said . It gave no details . The broadcast is expected to be start at 1400 GMT . The communist opposition charges that Yeltsin betrayed Russia ' s interests by compromising over NATO ' s plans to expand eastwards during his meeting with Clinton last week in Helsinki . Yeltsin dropped a previous demand that any deal Moscow concludes with NATO outlining ties with the Western defence alliance should be legally binding , saying instead that it should be politically binding only . 
